Title: An Act to Provide a Sales Tax Exemption for Housing Constructed
Official Title: An Act to Provide a Sales Tax Exemption for Housing Constructed
Number of Sections: 1
Source: versions - Documents and Disposition
Media Type: application/pdf
Strikethrough Detection: 2 sections found

================================================================================

Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1419
S.P. 575 In Senate, April 1, 2025
Off-site Similar to That for On-site Construction
Reference to the Committee on Taxation suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator BENNETT of Oxford.
Cosponsored by Speaker FECTEAU of Biddeford and
Senators: BICKFORD of Androscoggin, BRADSTREET of Kennebec, CURRY of Waldo,
PIERCE of Cumberland, Representatives: BLIER of Buxton, GERE of Kennebunkport,
GOLEK of Harpswell.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 36 MRSA §1760, sub-§40, ¶B, as amended by PL 2005, c. 618, §3, is
3 further amended to read:
4 B. New manufactured housing to the extent of all costs, other than materials, included
5 in the sale price, but the exemption may not exceed 50% 75% of the sale price.
6 Sec. 2. Application. This Act applies to sales of manufactured housing occurring on
7 or after January 1, 2026.
8 SUMMARY
99 Current law provides a sales tax exemption for sales of new manufactured housing for
1100 all costs, excluding materials, included in the sale price, but only to a maximum of 50% of
1111 the sale price. This bill changes that exemption to 75% of the sale price to reflect the
1122 exemption for housing built on the site of its location.
Page 1 - 132LR1063(01)
